{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"795e0448-4ce8-5b2a-8a85-3aa1ecac9c40","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5deece17-cd11-49fa-9c2f-a7f2018945f7 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 5deece17-cd11-49fa-9c2f-a7f2018945f7 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 3ff2fa3e-246f-4de6-8899-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 3e0d2efe-44f8-4ba8-a622-a7f2018945f7 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 3e0d2efe-44f8-4ba8-a622-a7f2018945f7 --><!-- begin field 6d0e7ead-4ca2-403a-9aa6-a7f2018945f7 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 6d0e7ead-4ca2-403a-9aa6-a7f2018945f7 --><!-- begin field 8b9fb2ad-dfb9-4a1b-8fc5-a7f2018945f7 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 8b9fb2ad-dfb9-4a1b-8fc5-a7f2018945f7 --><!-- begin field 3aca8377-70d6-4e82-a3ef-a7f2018945f7 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 3aca8377-70d6-4e82-a3ef-a7f2018945f7 --><!-- begin field 762dfe61-8b7b-4021-a0d4-a7f2018945f7 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 762dfe61-8b7b-4021-a0d4-a7f2018945f7 --><!-- begin field ef4b0a92-ea66-4ae1-9555-a7f2018945f7 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field ef4b0a92-ea66-4ae1-9555-a7f2018945f7 --><!-- end item 3ff2fa3e-246f-4de6-8899-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"26f48611-f890-5112-aa26-bef13e5623e1","topicId":"c9e197be-4f79-4d67-bf67-2b2a8a137e03","topicName":"MRSA in primary care","slug":"mrsa-in-primary-care","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2018","chapters":[{"id":"ba15ac05-528a-5474-8925-89cfea95b961","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"97d099f9-1263-51e7-8c71-fb82256182d3","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"f6df2380-e42f-563b-8f75-a588376e1da7","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"530a7f74-53c2-5e4e-8c1d-ceb01bccf776","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"a17267d5-eb08-5126-9312-b78fee4494a2","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"9537a389-c41a-5355-ac9c-9c56bba48a35","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"124fbaa7-2678-5958-b4be-d5f9be74c18a","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"4a1ce510-f22c-5132-a344-31bd40831eac","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"8e5d44fe-1deb-51e2-bb59-04ccc35710c7","slug":"audit-criteria","fullIte